commentTextItems.html: tossed up outside the off stump, Blackwell picks it up early and lofts it over long on fence, overstepping by the bowler and England wins by 5 wickets.
Great shot! fuller ball on the legs, Blackwell uses his feet and drives the ball wide on mid-on fielder, ball races to boundary rope, great timing

commentPostTextItems.html: England done it in style and win the match comprehensively. They are one up of 7 ODI series with one more game to play. Jamshedpur is once again become the non favourable venue for India and their winning percentace is very low here. Andrew Strauss came up with valint knock of 74 runs before he retired and gave the perfect start for England to chase a modest target. Then Kevin Pieterson and Paul Collingwood played a little cameo innings and make sure the required run rate comes below 4. Indian spinners manages to take the wickets and nothing left for the pacers. Andrews Strauss declared Man of the match for his fine innings. Please don't forgot to join with us for the last and 7th ODI between this teams. Till then bye from us.

stories.title: A breather for England
stories.subTitle: India v England, 6th ODI, Jamshedpur
stories.summary: England registered their first ODI win of the series, in conditions as different from those they are used to and most comfortable in, as is humanly possible

stories.title: Pitching it just right
stories.subTitle: India v England, 6th ODI, Jamshedpur
stories.summary: For the first time in the series, England's bowlers got a pitch which had some pace and bounce in it, and they made excellent use of the track
stories.byline: On the Ball with S Rajesh

stories.title: Sehwag and Kaif might miss Indore clash
stories.subTitle: India v England, 6th ODI, Jamshedpur
stories.summary: Virender Sehwag blamed a collective lack of application from the Indian top-order for the five-wicket defeat against England at Jamshedpur

stories.title: 'Our seamers did a very good job' says Strauss
stories.subTitle: India v England, 6th ODI, Jamshedpur
stories.summary: Andrew Strauss did much right on the day, scoring 74 and leading England to their first ODI victory of the series, but was typically modest and handed the credit to his bowlers

stories.title: Strauss stars in consolation win
stories.subTitle: India v England, 6th ODI, Jamshedpur
stories.summary: It took a testing spell from a trio of medium-pacers and a nuggety half-century from a stand-in stand-in captain to guide England to their first victory of the series

stories.title: Sizzling temperatures await teams
stories.subTitle: India v England, 6th ODI, Jamshedpur
stories.summary: From the hills of Guwahati where rains followed by the rage of disappointed fans put a dampener on this ODI series it is onto the industrial city of Jameshedpur in Jharkhand for the sixth ODI
stories.byline: The Preview by Anand Vasu in Jamshedpur

stories.title: A breather for England
stories.subTitle: India v England, 6th ODI, Jamshedpur
stories.summary: England registered their first ODI win of the series, in conditions as different from those they are used to and most comfortable in, as is humanly possible
